00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:17,000
 That's only possible when you choose the humble path.

534
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:22,000
 And our leadership will have the ability to go down this counter-cultural road

535
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:30,000
 of others focused, others first, by choosing humility.

536
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:37,000
 I think the temptation is that when we end up focusing on ourselves

537
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:42,000
 and measuring up to a metric that's ever-changing in our world,

538
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:45,000
 and I think that's what actually perpetuates the rat race.

539
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:47,000
 Like we're trying to become the best at this,

540
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:50,000
 but awesome in 2011 is different than awesome in 2015,

541
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:52,000
 which is different than awesome in 2022.

542
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:55,000
 Like greatness keeps changing.

543
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:57,000
 It's not in our favor to chase those things.

544
00:31:57,000 --> 00:31:58,000
 It keeps moving.

545
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:01,000
 It indeed becomes an actual rat race.

546
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:04,000
 And God is calling us out of that mentality,

547
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:07,000
 out of chasing the ever-changing system.

548
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:09,000
 Instead, by choosing humility,

549
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:12,000
 He's calling us to look at the other people,

550
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:13,000
 look at their worth.

551
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:16,000
 You know, He died for you, but He also died for them.

552
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:19,000
 The life, death, and resurrection of Jesus,

553
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:22,000
 His blood being spilled is for the person next to you,

554
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:24,000
 as well as you.

555
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:25,000
 That's something we have to remember.

556
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:28,000
 That gives our neighbor and those around us

557
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:35,000
 an inherent, limitless worth and value.

558
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:38,000
 The image of God is breathed into them

559
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:41,000
 as much as it's breathed into us.

560
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,000
 And I think by changing,

561
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:45,000
 by seeing things through this perspective,

562
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:48,000
 Jesus' model will change the way that we see people.

563
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:51,000
 It will no longer have that distorted,

564
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:52,000
 "What can they do for me?

565
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:54,000
 "How do they potentially help me progress?

566
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:56,000
 "What ways does this benefit me?"

567
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:58,000
 And it can just be about them.

568
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:02,000
 Just be about their good.

569
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:05,000
 This is the change that His model takes us through.

570
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:10,000
 This is where influence has a maximum impact.

571
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:14,000
 Jesus' model is just as much about influence

572
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:15,000
 as the world's model.

573
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:18,000
 But He approaches it from a completely different angle.

574
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:21,000
 See, true influence is not lording it over others.

575
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:24,000
 It's not viewing our neighbors as our competitor.

576
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:25,000
 It's not just looking out for me

577
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:27,000
 and my best friends and my family.

578
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:30,000
 No, true influence is serving others

579
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:37,000
 so that they might become more.

580
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:39,000
 I love that Jesus, in this passage,

581
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:42,000
 gives us this great theoretical concept,

582
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:45,000
 and then He ends it really beautifully

583
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:46,000
 by giving us a good example.

584
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:50,000
 He says, "The Son of Man, the King, God,

585
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:51,000
 "the One who created everything,

586
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:53,000
 "the One who everything belongs to,

587
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:55,000
 "the Christ who was preeminent above everything,

588
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,000
 "the firstborn of all creation,

589
00:33:56,000 --> 00:34:03,000
 "that guy came to serve and not to be served."

590
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:05,000
 He gives us a beautiful example

591
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:09,000
 of what humility in servant leadership looks like.

592
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:11,000
 And Paul would actually echo,

593
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:13,000
 and not just echo, he would expand this concept

594
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:15,000
 in Philippians 2, where he would say

595
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:17,000
 that Jesus did not see His godness,

596
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:20,000
 His divine right.

597
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:21,000
 He did not look at Himself in this space

598
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:22,000
 of I'm equal with God.

599
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:26,000
 He actually put that stuff to the side.

600
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:27,000
 He did not take, I think the very words,

601
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:29,000
 He did not take equality with God

602
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:33,000
 as something to be grasped.

603
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:35,000
 He wasn't looking for advantages for Him.

604
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:38,000
 He was looking for advantages for you.

605
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:41,000
 So instead, He emptied Himself.

606
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:42,000
 He put it to the side

607
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:44,000
 and He took on the form of a servant,

608
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:45,000
 and then Paul pushes it forward.

609
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:49,000
 He humbled Himself even to the point

610
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:53,000
 of death on a cross.

611
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:55,000
 For what?

612
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:58,000
 To make a point?

613
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:01,000
 But so that we might be reconciled to God.

614
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:06,000
 Like His leadership, His servanthood,

615
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:11,000
 and His slavery impacts you.

616
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:14,000
 It's the reason that we can be here

617
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:17,000
 and be close and near to God.

618
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:20,000
 It's the reason that we can have eternal life.

619
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:22,000
 It's the reason for our whole faith.

620
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:26,000
 What He did, assuming the lowest position possible,

621
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:29,000
 is how we were able to make it forward.

622
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:34,000
 That's His example of leadership.

623
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:36,000
 Counting the neighbor as more important.

624
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:38,000
 Paul would continue in Philippians.

625
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:40,000
 He would say, He would challenge us

626
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:43,000
 to do nothing out of selfish ambition,

627
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:45,000
 to not just focus on ourselves,

628
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:47,000
 but to look at the interest of others,

629
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:48,000
 not just our own,

630
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:51,000
 to take that mindset that Christ had in His humility.

631
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:54,000
 And we should use that in how we engage with others

632
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:56,000
 in leadership and in serving roles,

633
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:57,000
 becoming a servant to others.

634
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:59,000
 Jesus is changing.

635
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:01,000
 He's not changing leadership.

636
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:04,000
 He's just showing us how to do it the right way.

637
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:06,000
 And actually the most impactful way

638
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:08,000
 that the world's ever seen.

639
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:11,000
 And in Him, we have a model of humble leadership,

640
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:15,000
 a posture of humble relationships,

641
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:19,000
 a leader who serves the growth of others

642
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:22,000
 and the betterment of them and chooses humility.

643
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:25,000
 And there's a second way that I want to encourage us.

644
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:27,000
 So we choose humility as the first thing.

645
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:29,000
 The second thing is,

